    question: 'What is the Pomodoro Technique in simple terms?',
    answer: 'The Pomodoro Technique is a time management method where you work for 25 minutes on a single task with zero distractions, then take a 5-minute break. After completing 4 of these work sessions (called Pomodoros), you take a longer break of 15-30 minutes. The name comes from the tomato-shaped kitchen timer used by its creator, Francesco Cirillo, in the late 1980s.',
  },
